JOHANNESBURG - The Eastern Cape government wants the Public Protector's report into Nelson Mandela's funeral legally reviewed. The report looked at allegations of misappropriation of public funds during the former president's funeral.
	
	The Public Protector's report shows that the expenditure did not meet the necessary requirements. READ: Public Protector says law will take its course: Mandela funeral The provincial government maintains it did no wrong. It says it did not spend R300 million but under R40 million. The provincial government says this figure has been confirmed by the auditor general.  It's also denied that MEC of Treasury and Planning, Phumulo Masualle, benefitted from the funeral. eNCA